## Testing Requirements

### Test Phases (ordered -- never skip earlier phases)

| Phase | What | When to run |
|-------|------|-------------|
| **Unit** | Test individual functions/methods in isolation | Before and after every change |
| **Integration** | Test service interactions, DB queries, API calls | Before merging |
| **E2E** | Full user flows through the actual application | Before release |
| **Smoke** | Baseline validation under minimal load | After deployment |
| **Stress** | Find breaking points under heavy load | Before major releases |

### Test Naming and Organization

- **Naming:** `test_<function>_<scenario>` (e.g., `test_create_user_duplicate_email`)
- **Contract tests:** For external API integrations
- **Coverage:** Define your targets in CI configuration
- **Workflow:** Run existing tests → make changes → add new tests → run all again

{% if not custom_methodology %}
### Performance Targets (when applicable)

| Metric | Target |
|--------|--------|
| P50 latency | < 100ms |
| P95 latency | < 250ms |
| P99 latency | < 500ms |
| Error rate under normal load | < 0.1% |

### Test Data Rules

- Use factories or builders, not static fixtures
- Isolate test data per test run (unique prefixes or UUIDs)
- Clean up after integration/E2E runs
- Never use production data -- generate synthetic data matching schema constraints
